text: Antarches tessmanni is a moth of the family Pterophoridae that is known from Equatorial Guinea, Ghana, Guinea, Madagascar, South Africa, Uganda, Cameroon and Zimbabwe. The larvae feed on Cinchona pubescens. Ghana ==References== Category:Exelastini Category:Moths described in 1912 Category:Moths of Africa Category:Moths of Madagascar Category:Moths of Réunion
